AB  - This paper reviews and extends definitions and
                                                properties of the three classical performance
                                                statistics (the Sharpe Ratio, the Treynor Index, and
                                                Jensen's Alpha) by locating them in a more general
                                                framework: the Asymmetric Response Mode. This allows
                                                various notions of beta, which can be related to
                                                downside risk, to be employed, and includes, as
                                                special cases, a market timing model and the
                                                mean-variance CAPM. Due to the general lack of data
                                                on fund performance in practice, our emphasis is on
                                                small sample analysis where possible. We illustrate
                                                our results empirically using data on 15 U.S.-based
                                                emerging markets investment funds.
